## 1. Cascade overview

![Multicopter control cascade — uORB topic chain & injection points](mc_control_cascade_2026-06-01_cascade.svg)

Every stage is **event-driven** through `SubscriptionCallbackWorkItem`: when its primary input topic publishes, the work-queue scheduler invokes `Run()`. The triggering topic per stage:

| Module | Triggering subscription | Registration | dt clamp |
|---|---|---|---|
| `MulticopterPositionControl` | `_local_pos_sub` (`vehicle_local_position`) | `MulticopterPositionControl.cpp:65-72` (`registerCallback()` + `ScheduleNow()`) | ~2 ms - 40 ms |
| `MulticopterAttitudeControl` | `_vehicle_attitude_sub` | `mc_att_control_main.cpp:216` | 0.2 ms - 20 ms |
| `MulticopterRateControl` | `_vehicle_angular_velocity_sub` | `MulticopterRateControl.cpp:152` | 0.125 ms - 20 ms |
| `ControlAllocator` | `_vehicle_torque_setpoint_sub` **and** `_vehicle_thrust_setpoint_sub` | `ControlAllocator.cpp:93-101` (both registered) | 0.2 ms - 20 ms |

The two work-queues `nav_and_controllers` and `rate_ctrl` are separate PX4 work-queue threads with different priorities — the "fast" inner loop (rate control + allocator) runs at IMU-tick rate (~1 kHz), the "slower" outer loop (attitude + position) at attitude-estimator and local-position-estimator rates respectively.

