## 2. `vehicle_attitude_setpoint`

### 2.1 Message definition  (`msg/VehicleAttitudeSetpoint.msg`)

| Field | Type | Units / meaning |
|---|---|---|
| `timestamp` | `uint64` | µs since boot |
| `roll_body`, `pitch_body`, `yaw_body` | `float32` | Body Euler angles in NED — **for logging only**; quaternion `q_d` is the authoritative setpoint |
| `yaw_sp_move_rate` | `float32` | rad/s — feed-forward yaw rate |
| `q_d` | `float32[4]` | Desired attitude quaternion (the actual setpoint consumed by AttitudeControl) |
| `thrust_body` | `float32[3]` | Normalised thrust vector in body NED. For MC, `[0,0,-throttle]` — `thrust_body[2]` is the **negative** of throttle demand |
| `reset_integral` | `bool` | Cue to reset roll/pitch/yaw integrals (e.g. when navigation logic changes) |
| `fw_control_yaw_wheel` | `bool` | FW-only — irrelevant for MC |

Topic aliases declared in the `.msg`: `vehicle_attitude_setpoint`, `mc_virtual_attitude_setpoint`, `fw_virtual_attitude_setpoint`. The `*_virtual_*` aliases are used by VTOL when both MC and FW controllers run in parallel.

### 2.2 Publishers  (4 sites in the MC code paths)

| # | File:line | Function | Trigger / mode | Comment |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `mc_pos_control/MulticopterPositionControl.cpp:561` | `Run()` | Automated (any of position / velocity / altitude enabled) | The primary publisher — drives normal flight |
| 2 | `mc_att_control/mc_att_control_main.cpp:184` | `generate_attitude_setpoint()` | Stabilized / Manual-Attitude (`flag_control_manual && !alt && !vel && !pos`) | mc_att_control acts as **both** publisher and subscriber in this mode |
| 3 | `mavlink/mavlink_receiver.cpp:1573` | MAVLink `ATTITUDE_TARGET` handler | Offboard / external control | Used by companion-computer offboard mode |
| 4 | `mc_pos_control/MulticopterPositionControl.cpp:544-547` | `generateFailsafeSetpoint()` → `update()` → `:561` | Position-control update failure | Falls back to a safe local trajectory before publishing |

The publisher declaration is keyed to the vehicle type:

```cpp
// MulticopterPositionControl.cpp:48
_vehicle_attitude_setpoint_pub(vtol ? ORB_ID(mc_virtual_attitude_setpoint)
                                    : ORB_ID(vehicle_attitude_setpoint)),
```

