## 3. `vehicle_torque_setpoint` and `vehicle_thrust_setpoint`

### 3.1 Message definitions

**`msg/VehicleTorqueSetpoint.msg`**

| Field | Type | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| `timestamp` | `uint64` | µs since boot |
| `timestamp_sample` | `uint64` | sample timestamp (inherited from gyro) |
| `xyz` | `float32[3]` | Normalised body torque [-1, 1] |

Topic aliases: `vehicle_torque_setpoint`, `vehicle_torque_setpoint_virtual_fw`, `vehicle_torque_setpoint_virtual_mc`.

**`msg/VehicleThrustSetpoint.msg`**

| Field | Type | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| `timestamp`, `timestamp_sample` | `uint64` | as above |
| `xyz` | `float32[3]` | Normalised body thrust [-1, 1]. For MC, `[0,0,-throttle]`; `xyz[2]<0` = lift up |
| `flight_config`, `flight_config_last`, `surf_blend_100`, `swsh_blend_100` | `uint8` | configuration metadata for special airframes |

### 3.2 Publishers  (single MC publisher)

| # | File:line | Function | Mode that selects this branch |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `mc_rate_control/MulticopterRateControl.cpp:121-122` | `handle_manual_mode()` | Pure-manual passthrough (`!attitude && !rates`) — sticks → τ directly |
| 2 | `mc_rate_control/MulticopterRateControl.cpp:285,289` | `Run()` (PID rate-control path) | All hover modes where rates are stabilised |

The publisher is declared with topic-name dependent on the VTOL flag:

```cpp
// MulticopterRateControl.cpp constructor (vtol selects virtual_mc variants)
_vehicle_torque_setpoint_pub  = vtol ? ORB_ID(vehicle_torque_setpoint_virtual_mc)
                                     : ORB_ID(vehicle_torque_setpoint);
```

There is **no other module in the MC stack that publishes `vehicle_torque_setpoint` directly.** Other vehicle types (`fw_rate_control`, `airship_att_control`, `uuv_att_control`, `rover_pos_control`) have their own equivalent publishers. VTOLs publish to the `_virtual_*` aliases, and `vtol_att_control` then mixes them into the real `vehicle_torque_setpoint[0,1]` (dual-instance) for the allocator.

### 3.3 Subscribers

| # | File:line | Module | Comment |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `control_allocator/ControlAllocator.cpp:93,98` | `control_allocator` | **Primary consumer** — registered as callback at `init()` and ingested at `:371-388` |
| 2 | `ControlAllocator.hpp:177-178` | same module, instance 1 | Used only when `_num_control_allocation > 1` (VTOL dual-matrix mixers) |
| — | actuator_effectiveness tailsitter helpers | special VTOL mix logic | not a controller |

