## 4. `mc_pos_control` internals — *what produces `vehicle_attitude_setpoint`*

`Run()` body: `MulticopterPositionControl.cpp:321-582`. Triggered by `vehicle_local_position` callbacks; backup `ScheduleDelayed(100_ms)` ensures it runs even if the estimator stalls.

### 4.1 Inputs

| Subscription | File:line | Use |
|---|---|---|
| `vehicle_local_position` | `:99` (header) | feedback state — position, velocity, acceleration |
| `trajectory_setpoint` | `:104` | desired position / velocity / acceleration / yaw / yawspeed |
| `vehicle_control_mode` | `:106` | gates the control loop |
| `vehicle_constraints` | `:105` | tilt / velocity limits from FlightTask |
| `hover_thrust_estimate` | `:103` | online hover-thrust adaptation |
| `vehicle_land_detected` | `:107` | unblocks takeoff state machine |

### 4.2 `PositionControl::update()` math  (`PositionControl/PositionControl.cpp:108-122`)

Two cascaded P / PID loops with feed-forward, then a non-linear acceleration-to-thrust transformation.

**Position P controller**  (`:124-138`):
$$
\mathbf{v}_{sp,P} \;=\; (\mathbf{p}_{sp} - \mathbf{p}) \odot \mathbf{K}_p^{pos}
$$
Feed-forward $\mathbf{v}_{sp,ff}$ from `trajectory_setpoint.velocity` is added in (only if non-NaN). Horizontal magnitude is then constrained to $\|\mathbf{v}_{sp,xy}\| \le$ `MPC_XY_VEL_MAX`, vertical to `MPC_Z_VEL_MAX_UP/DN`.

**Velocity PID controller**  (`:140-202`):
$$
\mathbf{e}_v = \mathbf{v}_{sp} - \mathbf{v}, \qquad
\mathbf{a}_{sp,vel} \;=\; \mathbf{K}_p^{vel}\odot \mathbf{e}_v \;+\; \mathbf{v}_{int} \;-\; \mathbf{K}_d^{vel}\odot \dot{\mathbf{v}}
$$
The D-term subtracts the **measured** velocity derivative (not the error derivative — this prevents derivative kick on setpoint changes). Feed-forward $\mathbf{a}_{sp,ff}$ from `trajectory_setpoint.acceleration` is added in. Integrator update with anti-reset-windup (Rundqwist 1990):
$$
\mathbf{v}_{int} \mathrel{+}= \big(\mathbf{e}_v - g_{arw}\,(\mathbf{a}_{sp} - \mathbf{a}_{limited})\big)\odot \mathbf{K}_i^{vel} \, dt
$$
with $g_{arw} = 2/K_p^{vel,x}$.

**Acceleration → thrust direction**  (`:204-215`):
$$
\mathbf{b}_z \;=\; \text{normalize}\!\left( \begin{bmatrix} -a_{sp,x} \\ -a_{sp,y} \\ g \end{bmatrix} \right), \qquad
T_{coll} \;=\; \dfrac{a_{sp,z}\,H}{g} - H
$$
where $H$ is hover thrust (`MPC_THR_HOVER`, online-corrected by hover-thrust-estimate) and $g$ is gravity. Body Z is then tilt-limited to `_lim_tilt` against world Z. Collective thrust is rescaled by $1/(\hat{z}_W \cdot \mathbf{b}_z)$ to project it onto the planned body attitude.

**Quaternion construction**  (`ControlMath::bodyzToAttitude()` at `ControlMath.cpp:70-120`):

Given desired body Z and a yaw setpoint $\psi_{sp}$:
$$
\mathbf{y}_C = \begin{bmatrix} -\sin\psi_{sp} \\ \cos\psi_{sp} \\ 0 \end{bmatrix}, \quad
\mathbf{b}_x = \mathbf{y}_C \times \mathbf{b}_z, \quad
\mathbf{b}_y = \mathbf{b}_z \times \mathbf{b}_x
$$
$$
R_{sp} = \big[ \mathbf{b}_x \;\big|\; \mathbf{b}_y \;\big|\; \mathbf{b}_z \big], \quad
q_d = \mathrm{Quat}(R_{sp})
$$

### 4.3 Output

`getAttitudeSetpoint(attitude_setpoint)` at `PositionControl.cpp:259-263` fills the `vehicle_attitude_setpoint` message:

```cpp
ControlMath::thrustToAttitude(_thr_sp, _yaw_sp, attitude_setpoint);
attitude_setpoint.yaw_sp_move_rate = _yawspeed_sp;
```

`thrustToAttitude` (`ControlMath.cpp:47-51`) calls `bodyzToAttitude(-thr_sp, yaw_sp, att_sp)` and writes `thrust_body[2] = -|thr_sp|`. The publish call follows at `MulticopterPositionControl.cpp:561`.

