## 8. Mode routing — where each mode injects

![Mode routing — where each MC mode injects into the cascade](mc_control_cascade_2026-06-01_modes.svg)

| # | Mode | What flag(s) set the branch | Publisher of `vehicle_attitude_setpoint`? | Publisher of `vehicle_torque_setpoint`? | Injection stage |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Automated** (position / velocity / altitude) | any of `flag_control_{position,velocity,altitude}_enabled` | `mc_pos_control:561` | `mc_rate_control:289` (PID path) | INJ #1 + #2 — full cascade |
| 2 | **Stabilized / Manual-Attitude** | `flag_control_manual_enabled && !alt && !vel && !pos` (gated at `mc_att_control_main.cpp:289-296`) | `mc_att_control:184` (self-publishes from sticks via `generate_attitude_setpoint()`) | `mc_rate_control:289` | INJ #1 + #2 — skips pos_control |
| 3 | **MAVLink ATTITUDE_TARGET (offboard)** | external command from companion computer | `mavlink_receiver:1573` | `mc_rate_control:289` | INJ #1 + #2 — same as stabilized from the cascade's perspective |
| 4 | **Acro** (manual rate) | `flag_control_manual && !attitude` (gated at `MulticopterRateControl.cpp:183`) | — (no attitude setpoint generated) | `mc_rate_control:289` (with `_rates_setpoint` from sticks at `:189-205`) | INJ #2 only — skips mc_att_control |
| 5 | **Pure-Manual passthrough** | `flag_control_manual && !attitude && !rates` (gated at `:180`) | — | `mc_rate_control:121-122` via `handle_manual_mode()` | INJ #2 only — skips mc_att_control AND the PID rate loop |
| 6 | **Failsafe / Land** | failure of `_control.update(dt)` at `MulticopterPositionControl.cpp:540` | `mc_pos_control:561` (via `generateFailsafeSetpoint()`) | `mc_rate_control:289` | INJ #1 + #2 — degraded automated flight |

The **only path** that injects directly at INJ #2 without first going through mc_rate_control's PID is mode 5 (pure-manual). And even mode 5's publisher is still `mc_rate_control` itself, just via a different function (`handle_manual_mode()` instead of the `Run()` PID branch). So:

- **No mode bypasses `mc_rate_control` as a publisher.**
- **All modes ultimately reach `control_allocator`.** Only the *entry stage* of the cascade differs.

